cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a new data-driven approach to model hybrid systems that both flow and jump, using Neural Jump Stochastic Differential Equations. This approach extends the framework of Neural Ordinary Differential Equations, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves modeling temporal point processes, which is a common topic in the fields of statistics and information theory, falling under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper uses stochastic processes and neural networks, which are relevant to the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
